rComments: This was probably my hardest class to grasp so far in 3 years. However, I did really well in the course! Professor Reisz is such a friendly character. I never skipped one lecture, I always looked forward to obtaining new information from him! It's a lot of hard concepts to grasp, so Wiki is your friend!

okay prof. not really doing much teaching cuz he will just go over a bunch of slides w/o explaining much but it is anatomy so u either know it or u dont. he does make class fun with personal stories :)

dont be deceived by the positive remarks underneath. all those people that say rated him for bio210 from 2010 and earlier had him as a prof when it was still a half year course. i took it when it was a full year course and his detailed expectations were through the roof..but then again..it IS anatomy..

all the comments below me are from people that took BIO210 when it was being offered as a half year course. when i took it, it was the first time it was being offered as a full year course. during lecture, he would simply recite the text book to us and ocasionally throw in a couple of jokes. my level of interest in anatomy SHOT down because of him

Teaches alongside Dr. Lange and does the anatomy. Pretty funny guy, never puts down that mug for a second so no clue what's in it but it must be good lol. Very unambiguous and his part of the tests are really easy, just answer 2/3 anatomy diagrams but spelling counts. He takes really easy diagrams though.
Loved him. He's a great guy and his tests are fair.
Great Prof.  Ended up with an 89 in the course.  The stuff was really easy to memorize.  Just keep up with the readings and do the past tests and exams.

If BIO354 is not REQUIRED for this course, I don't understand why he speaks about the material as if the whole class has taken it. He needs to structure this course a lot better as most of the lectures, if not all of them, jump around and seem incoherent.

Awesome prof! Funny, makes everythign interesting and likes to share jokes and past life experiences that relate to lecture. Has a sever facination with evoultion that he throws in there also. The tests are fair but a lot to memorize! This is the one lecture ive had (im in 3rd year) that I have found extremely mandatory - he is just that helpful

taught with professor lange for this class....his anatomy lectures were SO interesting....so easy to understand and well-prepared....he knows what he's talking about...which i have to emphasize cuz not all profs hav that quality....his lectures are really helpful...pay full attention and take good notes....i swear u'd do good!

Love this prof! Course work is sometimes difficult..but he tries to make it easy. Focus on his lecture notes...for BIO354, I didn't even look at the textbook once and was getting 90s. BUT you HAVE to study his notes...can't "wing" the test. BIO354 labs were fun too...all dissection.
For some reason he doesn't like me even though I do well in his class. I have no idea what I did to offend him.
